** CALCULATOR Guides:

[1] How to declare a text area ?
<input type="text" id="textField" readonly>
Without closing tag it works. "readonly" makes it uneditable

[2] How to display value in a text field ?
document.querySelector('#textField').value='8';

[3] How to write inline javascript ?
<button class="button" onclick="
  currentDisplay = currentDisplay + '4';
  document.querySelector('#textField').value= currentDisplay;
">4</button>
<script>
  let currentDisplay=' ';
</script>

[4] How to decorate text field ?
#textField {
  margin: 10px;
  width: 85%;
}
"margin: 10px;" means charo aor se 10px ka jagah chhodega.
"width: 85%;" means div ke width ka 85% width occupy karega.

[5] How to prepare a responsive layout for buttons ?
.buttonDiv { 
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}
"flex" stands for flexible.
"display: flex" means buttons sud be flexible n responsive, will automatically wrap in next line if they already have eaten up all the horizontal allotted space.
" justify-content: center;" is applicable only for flex and grid containers. 